crops.description: Large, roundish, yellow with some green splashes and faint sparse netting, flesh white; not ripe when obtained.

Large, skin smooth, white with a few short green splashes; the largest one 29} by 21} inches in circumference, oval, the flesh white. A winter keeper, fit for preserving; not ripe when obtained. Brought from Charchan (No. 1), near Batoum.
Winter melon, round, yellow marbled with green. Originally from Crimea.
Oval, green and yellow marbled, smooth and very good; Persian.
Winter melon, center solid, flesh white (good); small, black, green-wrinkled. Crimean.

Tiflis-Erivan, No. 2. Oval, smooth, yellow, somewhat mottled with small dark-green spots, flesh white; very large, 30 by 23 inches in circumference. Not quite ripe when obtained, but sweet. A 'Doutjma' melon. See No. 739.
"Eichen " (oak). Large, roundish, dark green, marbled with faint yellowish, flesh white. Green when obtained, late keeper.
"Crimean pineapple." Oval, yellow with some green, marbly, white-fleshed, very good.
Winter, small, white, skin wrinkled, flesh white, center solid, very good. . Crimean (?).
Tiflis, No. 4. Oval, 28}.by 20 inches in circumference, bright yellow and smooth.
Tiflis, No. 1. Oval, 20} by 27 inches in circumference, skin longitudinally furrowed, white covered with short green splashes and spots, white-fleshed, not ripe when obtained; long-keeping.
